<Base title="Skills" activeNav="skills" description="221 structured reasoning skills for Claude Code, classified by universality.">
  <div class="page-header">
    <h1>Skills</h1>
    <p class="lead">221 structured reasoning skills for Claude Code. Each guides you through a specific type of thinking, classified by <a href="/about#universal-vs-heuristic">universality</a>.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="callout">
    <p><strong>Usage:</strong> type <code>/skillname your question</code> in a Claude Code session. For example: <code>/araw should I change careers</code></p>
  </div>

  <section>
    <h2><span class="tier-badge tier-exp">Experimental</span> ARAW, UAUA, GOSM</h2>
    <p>These use a different approach. They treat every claim as an unverified guess and test it by exploring what follows if it's right and what follows if it's wrong.</p>
    <div class="skill-grid">
      {experimental.map(s => (
        <a href={`/skills/${s.name}`} class="skill-item skill-item--link">
          <code>{s.name}</code> <span class="skill-title">- {s.title}</span>
          <div class="desc">{s.desc}</div>
        </a>
      ))}
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2><span class="tier-badge tier-1">Tier 1</span> Start here</h2>
    <p>The most generally useful skills. They work on almost any problem and consistently produce non-obvious results.</p>
    <div class="skill-grid">
      {tier1.map(s => (
        <a href={`/skills/${s.name}`} class="skill-item skill-item--link">
          <code>{s.name}</code> <span class="skill-title">- {s.title}</span>
          <div class="desc">{s.desc}</div>
        </a>
      ))}
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2><span class="tier-badge tier-2">Tier 2</span> Deep reasoning</h2>
    <p>Go deeper on specific types of thinking. Use when you need thoroughness on a particular kind of problem.</p>
    <div class="skill-grid">
      {tier2.map(s => (
        <a href={`/skills/${s.name}`} class="skill-item skill-item--link">
          <code>{s.name}</code> <span class="skill-title">- {s.title}</span>
          <div class="desc">{s.desc}</div>
        </a>
      ))}
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2><span class="tier-badge tier-3">Tier 3</span> Specialized tools</h2>
    <p>These solve specific types of problems well. Less general but very effective in their domain.</p>
    {tier3Categories.map(cat => (
      <div class="category-section">
        <h3>{cat.category}</h3>
        <div class="skill-grid">
          {cat.skills.map(s => (
            <a href={`/skills/${s.name}`} class="skill-item skill-item--link">
              <code>{s.name}</code> <span class="skill-title">- {s.title}</span>
            </a>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
    ))}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2><span class="tier-badge tier-4">Tier 4</span> Everything else</h2>
    <p>
      The remaining skills cover specific use cases: goal decomposition, procedure extraction, search methods, strategy discovery, self-auditing, and more.
      Browse <a href="https://github.com/benjam3n/reasoningtool/tree/main/claude-code-plugin/skills"><code>claude-code-plugin/skills/</code></a> for the complete list.
    </p>
  </section>
